What You Need to Know About This Project (the Short Story):
We want to offer our Medical & Motivation Account as a FREE iOS app for a better & more effective user experience.
We need to raise $12,000 in 30 days to pay for the app development to complete this goal - it's all about coding now!
The Medical & Motivation Account offers more than the traditional health apps acting only as electronic file cabinets. 
Yes, the Medical & Motivational Account can store the important, concrete details of your health. 
The Medical & Motivation Account also gives you the opportunity to contemplate questions and details about what’s going on  to help you create a foundation of knowledge (however strong you’re feeling to work towards). Giving more power back to the patient. (Did you know that even your fashion choice can affect how your appointment goes?)
The Medical & Motivation Account has been built recognizing that the user/patient has the potential of being the true expert on their health - the one who has to deal with any course of treatment decided on (the good, the bad and the ugly). Therefore, this person should have an opportunity to grow their voice in the decision-making process and on their own team. We want to help.
The Medical & Motivation Account has been created by Jenna, who has grown up in the healthcare system and knows what it takes to be a competent and confident patient (after making a lot of mistakes out of denial, resentment, and a yearning to be more than a patient in the eyes of society). She is now committed to using her experiences as a patient to become a better practitioner.
It comes with 9 sections: Symptoms (with a NEW Pain Tracker after project completion), Medication, Before My Appointment, My Appointment, Doctors, Surgery/Procedure, In Case of Emergency, Need to Know, Motivation.
The new Pain Tracker has been created with the guidance of those who deal with pain on a regular basis - Jenna wanted to go to the experts for that! 
We wanted to bring you a tool that accurately validates and communicates what it means to live with chronic pain, while working to maintain your quality of life. It is highly customizable, so that you can then see and show others who can offer the right support what pain looks like and feels to you, which gives you the best chance to find the right help. You'll be able to assign different pain types with a colour and use your finger or a stylus to show exactly where it hurts on the outline of a body provided. Ultimately, we want the app to take that data and turn it into a chart so you can see how pain affects your life, potentially seeing patterns and a new game strategy!
Our Medication section has become more comprehensive, giving you the opportunity to get notifications and reminders to take your meds and how much. It goes further to support those of you with more complex regimes that might come about during Cancer treatments, because the stress of keeping up with everything is that last thing you need!
We have also worked to make sure you can get reminders and notifications of upcoming appointments, so you can focus on getting ready - mind, body, and spirit - for those appointments and make the most out of them.
How This Professional Patient-Turned-Practitioner Was Inspired to Create the Medical & Motivation Account (the Longer Story):Holed up in intensive care not too long ago, I came within a hair’s breadth of seeing “the light” from an out-of-control infection (stacked onto some other problems). While I’d been in the hospital many times before, this last visit easily crowned the stress chart. I’d had to be relentless in dealing with the medical staff, I felt mostly ignored as I voiced my concerns, and it was only a hysterical outburst on my part that finally got me the attention – and the emergency surgery right in my room – that I needed. It also left me with another little bonus - full-blown Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder. Ta da! I’d hit bottom.Rock? Bottom has redeeming features, though! I realized clearly that it was my ability to advocate for myself (not easy when you don’t like bothering people) that had saved my life. I also realized how many lessons I’d learned over the years that could not only help me, if I crunched them into a system, but could help so many others (including parents of children with medical needs) who were just starting their medical odyssey or hadn’t been in the kiln quite as long.These experiences as a patient trying and learning to navigate the healthcare system are enriched by my work as a registered social worker with a Master's of Social Work degree. I see how to effectively navigate the system and the support that can make the biggest impact. I have an understanding of what patients need from their practitioners, and what practitioners need from their patients. Therefore, you learn a variety of lessons: how to be assertive, not aggressive; how to better communicate your (the various items in a list need to have parallel structure) needs and ability; tips and tricks like how your outfit can impact your appointment and what you can do to keep calm and resilient as a patient; and how to continue growing and evolving into a competent and confident patient. Learn more about Phoenix Attitude's founder, Jenna Why We're Asking for Your Help:Until now the Medical & Motivation Account has been offered through our mobile-friendly website. However, as so many of us rely on our phones to improve our quality of life with ease, using the website is most effective for computer use. In fact, the most frequent question we get is if there is a Medical & Motivation Account app. We're dedicated to providing a better solution that is easy to use, effective and empowering. We think this what healthcare tools should be, not ones that fuel resentment for having health challenges and ultimately leave us frozen in denial. We need to transition the Medical & Motivation Account from a mobile-friendly web tool to an app (iOS, hoping to offer an Android version in the future). In doing so, we expect more people - like you - will be willing to put in the work and become the expert on yourselves. Your health challenges don't define you - you're unique and have the potential to impact the world. The last thing you want is to be sidelined by your health challenges longer than necessary. (I know writing in active is better than passive, but “are” is incorrect because you’re talking about “the last thing” (which is singular) are your health challenges sidelining you longer than necessary.What the App Would Include: The Medical & Motivation Account is made up of 9 sections coming together to give you the ability to engage with your health in a meaningful way: 
In Case of Emergency; 
Need to Know; 
Doctors; 
Medication; 
Symptoms featuring our new Pain Tracker; 
Surgeries/Procedures; 
Before My Appointment; 
My Appointment; 
MOTIVATION 
These sections don't just focus on your body, but your mind and spirit, too, as I see them so interrelated.Each section helps you create a foundation of knowledge to build on (as much or as little as you want) to make the most of your healthcare experience. Using it helps you understand what works for you and what doesn't, making you more confident and assertive about how you're treated. You realize how valuable it is to have concrete information on how your body is working at your fingertips ready to be a part of recovering quicker! Finally, you're offered the potential to not only support your body, but fortify your mind and spirit, too. As before, you can share parts of your Medical & Motivation Account with your support network who also have an account. You always have the option of rescinding access, and their access is read-only so the information can't be altered.Because we want this app to help you in every possible way, we even put significant thought into the colour scheme and decided that a bright, colourful design would be best. Even the colour scheme was a conscious choice for the Medical & Motivation Account! It's colourful! That's right, we didn't want (what I hope becomes) your new healthcare sidekick to make you feel like you're stuck in the often-sterile white walls of the hospital or the doctor's office - I wanted you to be reminded of the vibrant person you are! The Motivation section has been built so that you can have a laugh when you're having a bad day or need a distraction, to inspire you, to motivate you, to give you hope, and so that you can see how other people cope and thrive (you didn't think you were alone, did you?).Our Goal:To build this app for iOS and include our new pain tracker we need $12,000. We are hoping to achieve this goal in 30 days so that we can start development, which will take 12-16 weeks. We are working with developers in Toronto to bring this project to life, who have successfully delivered 1000+ projects from small websites to complex international portals, from online shops to mobile apps, from software solutions to digital marketing services. What's New & Exciting That Will be Available on the App: We are adding more in-depth functionality in the Medication section so users can have reminders emailed to you or have a notification pop up on your iOS device. We are also working to better support people with more complex medication regimes that require different dosages of a medication at different times of the day, as well as letting users know when it's time to stop a medication and begin a new one another one. We are also building a Pain Tracker in the Symptoms section so you can get a better understanding of your pain and more effectively communicate it. With this new tool you can assign your pain a colour then fill in the outline of a body provided in the corresponding area (no matter how many different kinds of pain you experience). This data will then be available to you in charts you can track over a day, week, month, and year. This is meant to track patterns and therefore help you better treat the pain more efficiently.Finally, users will be offered the ability to get reminders emailed to them or as a notification on your iOS device for upcoming appointments!Testimonials:New Health Challenges - As an active, 30-year-old woman, I had been healthy my whole life. Very recently I was thrown a curve ball, and having no previous experience with serious health concerns, my new reality was very distressing and overwhelming. Phoenix Attitude proved vital in helping me navigate this unexpected and highly emotionally-charged situation by preparing me for appointments with my doctors, and providing the right tools for me to get all of my important information down during and after these appointments, to be able to draw upon it whenever I may need in the future. I only wish I had taken advantage of all this site has to offer sooner, rather than waiting for a crisis situation. I highly recommend Phoenix Attitude to anyone who wants to be proactive about their health. Thank you, Phoenix Attitude! Caregiver - Phoenix Attitude has changed my life for the better. As a professional caregiver it enables me to easily input my client’s important health information and share it with their family. I like being able to give my elderly clients’ children the opportunity to stay involved, even if they’ve moved away and are raising their own family. With the Medical & Motivation account, distance does not have to impede families taking care of each other.Daughter - I am the daughter of a mother with an acquired brain injury. This sudden illness resulted in an extended hospital stay and a flurry of appointments with doctors whose specialties I had never even heard of. This was overwhelming and scary for me, as an 18 year old, and for my siblings. During that time, many questions were put to us that, as her children, we had never considered and couldn’t begin to answer. During those early years we were carried along in a flow of confusion, fear and barely understood medical terminology. We didn’t know what questions to ask or even how to understand the answers to the questions we were able to ask. Now, almost 14 years on I am still going to appointments with my mother, but today I attend those appointments as my mother’s advocate. My mother is a strong, intelligent and fiercely independent woman whose aphasia, all too often, causes doctors and service providers to attempt to talk over her or look to us for answers to their questions.  Having the opportunity to explore the Medical & Motivation Account created by Phoenix Attitude was incredible. I felt relief. Relief that I would no longer have to be a ‘custodian’ of my mother’s medical history; relief that something ‘small’ wouldn’t be forgotten or overlooked in the face of ‘larger’ issues; relief that my mother could have some control over her own medical journey.  The account is easy to use and to personalize. All too often when faced with a form I find myself wondering what to write, but the prompts and options provided offer the direction, while not limiting the user to a ‘form answer’. Having the ability to record a wide range of experience and information in a single place is reassuring for my mother, but also for her children. We know that the information is compiled and accessible if we need it.As the daughter of a medically complex parent I highly recommend the Medical & Motivation Account created by Phoenix Attitude. It has given my mother control of her own medical journey and her children a sense of relief. Thank you Phoenix Attitude!
